sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant K as Kafka
    participant S as Spark (Silver)
    participant CP as Checkpoint (S3)
    participant IB as Iceberg (silver)

    S->>CP: read committed offsets
    S->>K: fetch batch [o_start, o_end)
    K-->>S: change events
    S->>S: dedup by PK, order by LSN
    S->>IB: MERGE INTO (idempotent, LSN-guarded)
    IB-->>S: snapshot committed (atomic)
    S->>CP: commit offsets = o_end
    Note over S,IB: If crash before offset commit,<br/>batch replays; MERGE is idempotent<br/>→ effectively exactly-once
